// Fixture for task 4789 (cost-min α): robustness floor signal.
//
// CostMinFloor has one `Length = auto` param `thickness` and a fixed
// `Money = 5USD` param `unit_cost`.  The constraint `thickness > 1mm`
// places a strict lower bound; the money-dimensioned objective
// `minimize unit_cost * (thickness / 1mm)` drives the optimizer TOWARD
// that lower boundary.
//
// Without the robustness floor, the strict `>` boundary causes the
// solver to park at/below 1mm (infeasible or exactly on the boundary).
// With the floor (α deliverable), the synthetic constraint
//   slack(thickness > 1mm) = thickness − 1mm ≥ m
// pushes the resolved value to thickness ≈ 1mm + m (≈ 1.02mm) — strictly
// OFF the boundary, satisfying the strict `>`.
//
// Integration test: crates/reify-eval/tests/robustness_floor_signal.rs
//   asserts thickness > 1mm (= 0.001 m) AND thickness < 1.5mm (= 0.0015 m)
//   and result.diagnostics contains code == RobustnessFloorApplied (Info).
structure CostMinFloor {
    param thickness: Length = auto
    param unit_cost: Money = 5USD

    constraint thickness > 1mm

    minimize unit_cost * (thickness / 1mm)
}
